name: naphthalene, 2-methoxy-
Reason: The compound 2-methoxynaphthalene is based on the structure of naphthalene with an additional methoxy group (-OCH3). Starting with naphthalene, which has a melting point of 80 degrees Celsius, the effect of the methoxy group needs to be considered. Methoxy groups are known to donate electron density through resonance to the aromatic ring, which generally increases the melting point due to stronger pi-pi interactions and potential hydrogen bonding. However, the introduction of an oxygen atom also adds steric hindrance, which might slightly reduce the melting point as it can disrupt the crystal packing. Considering these factors, the addition of a methoxy group is predicted to have a modest increasing effect on the melting point, roughly around -6.5 degrees Celsius, when compared to naphthalene.
